<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2, img, p { margin: 0; } td { padding-top: 0 !important; } p { margin-bottom: 10px; } </mj-style>
    <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" />
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3">
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer> 
    <!-- Logo Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff"> 
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/logo.png" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" alt="" />
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              margin-top:2px;
            ">Did you know the President of the United States receives a top-secret briefing on national security every morning?</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            "><strong>In today’s weekend edition:</strong></p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4; 
              padding-left:10px;
            ">→ Lunar New Year</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left:10px;
            ">→ Gulf of America</p>
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
              padding-left:10px;
            ">→ Thai’s tourism frustration</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>
    <!-- THE BIG ONE-->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="2px 12px 0px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          padding-top:14px;
          color:#4D3060;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom:2px solid #4D3060;
            text-transform:uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
              padding-bottom:8px;
            ">SPOTLIGHT OF THE WEEK</h2>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- THE BIG ONE contents-->
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Musk nominated for the Nobel Peace Prize</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-feb-1-1.png" alt="Musk nominated for the Nobel Peace Prize" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">

          <!-- <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4"><strong>Summary: Trump’s first week of presidency saw him issue many executive orders, which reflected his campaign promises.</strong></p> -->

          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">Slovenian MEP member Branko Grims has nominated nominated Elon Musk for the 2025 Nobel Peace Prize. Grims announced the nomination in recognition of Musk's advocacy for free speech, particularly his acquisition of Twitter (now rebranded as X) and his efforts to support the platform as a space for open dialogue (<a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-01-02-2025-spotlight-see-interview?source=website" target="_blank">see interview</a>).</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;filter:blur(5px);">However, this is not the first time he has been nominated for the Nobel Peace Prize; he was <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-01-02-2025-spotlight-nominated-last-year?source=website" target="_blank">nominated last year</a>, along with Donald Trump and Greta Thunberg. The names of Nobel Peace Prize nominees are not officially released until 50 years after the prize is given out. Any national assembly member can nominate anyone for the award, and there were 286 nominations for the <a href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-01-02-2025-spotlight-2024-noble-peace-prize?source=website" target="_blank">2024 Nobel Peace Prize</a>.</p>
        </mj-text> 
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>